# Vue component conventions

## File locations and naming

All field view components live in `plugins/baserow_color_field/web-frontend/components/`. Baserow expects specific component roles; names must follow the pattern:

| Component | Role |
|-----------|------|
| `GridViewFieldColor.vue` | Inline editable cell in the grid view |
| `FunctionalGridViewFieldColor.vue` | Read-only (functional) render of the grid cell |
| `RowEditFieldColor.vue` | Field editor inside the row expand modal |
| `RowCardFieldColor.vue` | Compact read-only swatch on card/kanban views |
| `ColorPickerPopup.vue` | Shared **sliders-only** popup (patched `vue-accessible-color-picker`; hex is edited in the grid cell or row chip, not in the popup) |

When adding a new component, wire it in `fieldTypes.js` via the matching getter (e.g. `getGridViewFieldComponent()`).

## Styling

- Use **unscoped** `<style>` blocks with BEM-like class prefixes scoped by field name:
  - `.grid-field-color`, `.grid-field-color__display`, `.grid-field-color__swatch`
  - `.row-edit-field-color`, `.row-edit-field-color__picker`
  - `.color-picker-popup`, `.color-picker-popup--row-modal`
- Layout variations between grid popup and row modal are handled via a `layout` prop (`"default"` vs `"row-modal"`) with modifier classes.
- Avoid `!important` unless overriding third-party library defaults from `vue-accessible-color-picker`.

## Color picker integration

- `ColorPickerPopup.vue` wraps `<ColorPicker>` from `vue-accessible-color-picker` with `:visible-formats="['hex']"` as a safety net.
- The **shipped** bundle omits the library’s text/format row (hex/HSL inputs, format switch): `scripts/patch-vue-accessible-color-picker.js` runs after `yarn add` in the Docker build and edits `dist/ColorPicker.js` so only the 2D area and sliders remain.
- **Hex8** is shown and edited in `GridViewFieldColor` / `RowEditFieldColor`; the popup is for picking only. Hex8 ↔ internal color conversion happens in `ColorPickerPopup` (and handlers that call it).
- The popup communicates via `v-model` (hex string) and a `@close` event.

## Dependencies

- `vue-accessible-color-picker` (pinned major in the Dockerfile) and `colorjs.io` are installed during the Docker frontend build stage (`yarn add` in the Dockerfile), not in the plugin's own `package.json`. The patch script is part of that build; bumping the picker version may require adjusting anchors in the script.
